GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
SESSION 2025
S 2
SENATE BILL 400
Judiciary Committee Substitute Adopted 4/30/25
Short Title: Adult Protection Multidisciplinary Teams. (Public)
Sponsors:
Referred to:
March 25, 2025
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT CONCERNING THE ESTABLISHMENT OF LOCAL ADULT PROTECTION
3 MULTIDISCIPLINARY TEAMS.
4 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
5 SECTION 1. Chapter 108A of the General Statutes is amended by adding a new
6 Article to read:
7 "Article 6B.
8 "Local Adult Protection Multidisciplinary Teams.
9 "§ 108A-118. Declaration of public policy; purpose.
10 (a) The General Assembly finds that it is the public policy of this State to prevent the
11 abuse, neglect, and exploitation of disabled adults and older adults. The General Assembly
12 further finds that professionals from disparate disciplines have expertise that can promote the
13 safety and well-being of disabled adults and older adults and prevent re-victimization and that
14 multidisciplinary reviews of selected cases can lead to a greater understanding of the causes of
15 the abuse, neglect, and exploitation of disabled adults and older adults. It is, therefore, the intent
16 of the General Assembly, through this Article, to promote the establishment of local adult
17 protection multidisciplinary teams.
18 (b) The purpose of this Article is to authorize local adult protection multidisciplinary case
19 review teams to share information pertaining to selected cases in which disabled adults and older
20 adults are being served by adult protective services and to coordinate multiagency solutions for
21 adult victims of abuse, neglect, and exploitation.
22 "§ 108A-118.1. Definitions.
23 The following definitions apply in this Article:
24 (1) Case Review Multidisciplinary Team. – An adult protection multidisciplinary
25 team that reviews selected active cases in which disabled adults and older
26 adults are being served by adult protective services through a local department
27 of social services.
28 (2) Director of social services. – As defined by G.S. 108A-74.
29 (3) Disabled adult. – An individual 18 years of age or older or a lawfully
30 emancipated minor who is present in the State of North Carolina and who is
31 physically or mentally incapacitated, as defined in G.S. 108A-101(d).
32 (4) Older adult. – An individual 65 years of age or older.
33 (5) Systemic Review Multidisciplinary Team. – An adult protection
34 multidisciplinary team that works together to do all of the following:
*S400-v-2*

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 a. Address systemic problems and service gaps that may exist in the
2 delivery of services to disabled adults or older adults by public and
3 nonpublic agencies.
4 b. Develop information networks.
5 c. Provide coordinated community education and outreach designed to
6 protect against abuse, neglect, and exploitation of disabled adults or
7 older adults.
8 "§ 108A-118.2. Case Review Multidisciplinary Team; creation and composition.
9 (a) Creation. – Each county may establish its own Case Review Multidisciplinary Team
10 or participate in a multicounty Case Review Multidisciplinary Team, as determined in
11 accordance with subsection (b) of this section.
12 (b) Determination of Single County Versus Multicounty Case Review Multidisciplinary
13 Team. – Each county board of commissioners may evaluate and determine whether the county
14 will establish its own Case Review Multidisciplinary Team or become part of a multicounty team.
15 This determination shall be made in consultation with the director of the local department of
16 social services. A multicounty Case Review Multidisciplinary Team may be formed upon
17 agreement of the county boards of commissioners of each of the counties involved. The board of
18 commissioners of a county that is a member of a multicounty Case Review Multidisciplinary
19 Team may choose to withdraw from the multicounty Case Review Multidisciplinary Team upon
20 prior written notice to the boards of county commissioners of all other counties that are members
21 of the multicounty Case Review Multidisciplinary Team.
22 (c) Mandatory Members. – Each single county Case Review Multidisciplinary Team
23 shall consist of the following persons identified in subdivisions (1) through (11) of this
24 subsection, and each multicounty Case Review Multidisciplinary Team shall consist of the
25 following persons identified in subdivisions (1) through (11) of this subsection from each county
26 represented on that multicounty team:
27 (1) The director of social services.
28 (2) A staff member of the local department of social services, designated by the
29 director of social services.
30 (3) A local law enforcement officer, appointed by the board of county
31 commissioners after consultation with the district attorney's office and the
32 local department of social services.
33 (4) An attorney from the district attorney's office, appointed by the district
34 attorney.
35 (5) The public guardian appointed in the county by the clerk of superior court
36 under Article 11 of Chapter 35A of the General Statutes.
37 (6) A local mental health professional, appointed by the director of the area
38 authority established under Chapter 122C of the General Statutes.
39 (7) The long-term care ombudsman serving in the county, to be appointed by the
40 Office of the State Long-Term Care Ombudsman.
41 (8) The director of the local department of public health or a member of the
42 director's staff, as designated by the director.
43 (9) A local health care provider, appointed by the local board of health.
44 (10) A representative from the local area agency on aging, appointed by the
45 director of the area agency on aging serving the county.
46 (11) A victim advocate from a local domestic violence or sexual assault agency,
47 appointed by the agency's executive director.
48 (d) Members Appointed by the Chair. – The chair of the Case Review Multidisciplinary
49 Team may appoint a maximum of five additional members representing local agencies or the
50 community at large to serve on any Case Review Multidisciplinary Team, including, but not
Page 2 Senate Bill 400-Second Edition

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 limited to, representatives from financial institutions, local hospitals, and nonprofit
2 organizations.
3 (e) Vacancies. – Vacancies on a Case Review Multidisciplinary Team shall be filled by
4 the original appointing authority.
5 (f) Chair. – Each Case Review Multidisciplinary Team shall elect a member to serve as
6 chair at the pleasure of the Case Review Multidisciplinary Team. Within three months after being
7 elected as chair, the chair shall participate in the appropriate training developed under
8 G.S. 108A-118.5.
9 (g) Meetings. – Each Case Review Multidisciplinary Team shall meet at least four times
10 each year. The director of the local department of social services shall call the first meeting of
11 the Case Review Multidisciplinary Team. Thereafter, the chair of each Case Review
12 Multidisciplinary Team shall schedule the time and place of meetings, in consultation with the
13 director of the local department of social services, and shall prepare the agenda. The chair shall
14 schedule meetings no less often than once per quarter and often enough to allow adequate review
15 of the cases selected for review. The Case Review Multidisciplinary Team may conduct meetings
16 despite vacancies, absences, or failure to appoint a member.
17 "§ 108A-118.3. Case Review Multidisciplinary Team; powers and duties.
18 Each Case Review Multidisciplinary Team established pursuant to this Article has the
19 following powers and duties:
20 (1) To review, in accordance with the written operating procedures established by
21 the director of the local department of social services under G.S. 108A-118.4,
22 selected active cases in which disabled adults or older adults are being served
23 by adult protective services through the local department of social services.
24 (2) To submit annually to the board of county commissioners recommendations,
25 if any, for addressing systemic problems and service gaps that may exist in
26 the delivery of services to disabled adults and older adults by public and
27 nonpublic agencies.
28 "§ 108A-118.4. Case Review Multidisciplinary Team; duties of the director of the local
29 department of social services.
30 (a) In addition to any other duties as a member of the Case Review Multidisciplinary
31 Team, and in connection with the reviews conducted under G.S. 108A-118.3(1), the director of
32 the local department of social services has the following powers and duties:
33 (1) To assure the development of written operating procedures in connection with
34 these reviews, including frequency of meetings, confidentiality policies,
35 training of members, and duties and responsibilities of members.
36 (2) To assure that the Case Review Multidisciplinary Team defines the categories
37 of cases that are subject to its review.
38 (3) To bring for review active cases selected by the director of the local
39 department of social services or requested by a member of the Case Review
40 Multidisciplinary Team in which a disabled adult or older adult is being served
41 by adult protective services.
42 (4) To provide staff support for these reviews.
43 (5) To maintain records, including minutes of all official meetings, lists of
44 participants for each meeting of the team, and signed confidentiality
45 statements required under G.S. 108A-118.7, in compliance with applicable
46 State laws and rules.
47 (6) To report annually to the local board of social services, or as otherwise
48 required by the board, on the activities of the Case Review Multidisciplinary
49 Team.
